<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-59-0471 </DOCNO><TEXT>In 40 patients undergoing pre-treatment for an ovarian tumor, a CT scanof the pelvis and measurements of their CA 125, CA 19 - 9, IAP (immunosupressiveacidic antigen), and TPA (tissue polypeptide antigen were performed.The specificity and sensitivity of the CT diagnosis was found to be betterthan any of other tumor markers measurements. Comparison of the 4 markersshowed that the CA 125 testing had the greatest sensitivity in detectingan ovarian cancer. Moreover, the sensitivity of CA 125, was better thana combination of the 4 markers. Thus, a CT scan still remains necessaryfor the diagnosis of an ovarian cancer.</TEXT></DOC>